The paper proposes a model predictive controller for battery energy storage systems to reduce demand charge cost and enhance PV-utilization level simultaneously. This involves the use of control theory and optimization techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of batteries for stacked services, which involves the integration of multiple functions and can be related to the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with energy management and optimization, which can be associated with the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses load patterns and battery size optimization, which can be related to the cs.EM (Electric Machines and Drives) sub-category.
